## 3. The reference frames vs the reference content

`corpus.commons/demo/references/REFERENCE-INDEX.md` and each per-task distillation index (`aar`, `decision-making`, `retro`, `software-business`, `stakeholder-engagement`) are mixed: the structural frames (section headings, format documentation, anti-pattern lists) are substrate and ship under `LICENSE` (MIT); the entries pointing at third-party-derived files are summaries of material under the upstream licences listed above.

In practice, treat each whole index file as carrying the most restrictive licence present among its entries (currently CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, because both OpenStax NC-SA titles and the *Org Topologies Primer* are indexed across the task axes). After removing every NC-class source, the indexes effectively carry CC BY-SA 4.0 because of the ShareAlike entries (Jones, Scrum Guide, SSDL); after removing those too, the frames stand on their own under MIT.

