## Licence vs distribution scope

This file records *licence* (upstream legal status, drives attribution and derivative-rights). Each deep reference also carries a *scope* (`open`, `open-nc`, `copyrighted`, `confidential`, `personal`), which drives the build's mechanical distribution filter via each profile's `max_scope` ceiling. The two usually correlate (CC BY → `open`, CC BY-NC-SA → `open-nc`, all-rights-reserved → `copyrighted`) but can diverge. For example, a CC BY paper used inside a confidential client engagement carries Licence `CC BY 4.0` and Scope `confidential`. The build excludes references whose scope exceeds a profile's `max_scope`; `personal` ships in no profile. Full taxonomy and behaviour: [README.md](README.md#distribution-scope) and [docs/architecture/copyright.md](docs/architecture/copyright.md).
